==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Avaunt
<hw>A*vaunt"</hw> <pr>(⟦adot⟧*v⟦add⟧nt" <it>or</it>
⟦adot⟧*v⟦aum⟧nt")</pr>, <pos>interj.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>avant</ets>
forward, fr. L. <ets>ab</ets> + <ets>ante</ets> before. Cf.
<er>Avant</er>, <er>Advance</er>.]</ety> <def>Begone; depart; -- a word
of contempt or abhorrence, equivalent to the phrase ⟦ldquo⟧Get thee
gone.⟦rdquo⟧</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Avaunt</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Avaunt
<hw>A*vaunt"</hw>, <pos>v. t. & i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To advance; to
move forward; to elevate.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To depart; to move away.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Coverdale.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Avaunt</ent>⟦br⟧

